sec.p:
Because it still has a high temperature, the pre-evaporated broth should be cooled again to 30 °C using cold water to suit the conditions of the fermentation medium. In this step of must preparation, the yeasts become stressed if the must reaches the vat at a very high temperature, and the fermentation yield for ethanol production will be lower. Therefore, it is necessary to remove more energy from the must (Eq. (11)):11Qcoolingbroth=mpre-evapbroth.∫68,730Cppre-evapbroth=-4.068.020,16kcalh\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
